*****
[2] Cholera - Zambia (Lusaka Province)
Date: Fri 12 Feb 2016
Source: Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation (ZNBC) [edited]
http://www.znbc.co.zm/?p=31200


Ministry of Health Acting Spokesperson Tasila Pitters says 13 people are currently admitted to Kanyama Cholera treatment center [Lusaka Province]. Dr Pitters has since advised the public to enhance self-hygiene such as washing hands with clean water. She pointed out that there is need for the public to avoid unnecessary handshakes and public gatherings during the cholera outbreak period.

Meanwhile, Dr Pitters says a cholera treatment center has been set up at Kanyama health center for isolation and treatment of cholera patients. She said an emergency epidemic preparedness committee was held today at the Ministry with stakeholders to respond to the outbreak.

This is the 1st time Lusaka has a cholera outbreak since the year 2010.

