[3] Cholera, diarrhea - India (Assam State)
Date: Thu 11 Feb 2016
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/guwahati/6-die-of-cholera-diarrhoea/articleshow/50942109.cms


Cholera and diarrhea have so far claimed 6 lives in Lakhipur sub-division of Cachar district [Assam State], health officials said on Wed 10 Feb 2016. The deaths were reported from Dilkush tea garden and Dungripar locality. Cachar district joint director of health Sudip Jyoti Das said 2 of the deaths were due to cholera. This was confirmed after tests were conducted at Silchar Medical College and Hospital [SMCH]. The patients were admitted to SMCH after they were struck by diarrhea, he said. Sources said while 12 patients of the area suffering from diarrhea are admitted to SMCH, more are being treated at their home. Contaminated water is believed to be the reason for the spread of cholera and diarrhoea in Lakhip.

